2004: A powerful earthquake on the west coast of the Indonesian province of Aceh, North Sumatra, on December 26, triggered a tsunami that struck 14 countries, killing 226,000 along the Indian Ocean coastline, and more than half of those killed died in the tsunami.
2005: A series of powerful earthquakes hit the west coast of Sumatra in late March and early April.
